data.reddit:
Age: 20
Height: 5’10
Weight: 145 lbs
Sex: Female
Medication: none
Past conditions: UTI, Chlamydia 
Ethnicity: African American

The other day I got a call from my Doctor’s office telling me that my blood test from my yearly checkup indicated that I had a low white blood cell count. They also told me that I needed to schedule another appointment for another blood test, to ensure that there wasn’t a mistake.

Two months or so before this I visited an urgent care with some vaginal discomfort (I thought it was a yeast infection) where they told me that my urine test indicated that I had a UTI and might be pregnant (even when I had already had three periods since the last time I had unprotected sex with my bf). They wanted me to do a blood test that day to confirm the pregnancy result, but I was in a rush and refused. They treated me for the UTI and needless to say, I ended up not being pregnant.

A week after this visit, they called me back and told me that I had Chlamydia. They quickly treated me for this. I told my boyfriend, he went to get tested for STDs, and also ended up having Chlamydia (but nothing else)

I am hoping that my low white blood cell count is a product of having Chlamydia that I didn’t know about. But, honestly, this whole situation is just stressing me out. Why do I need to take another blood test? Why can’t you just tell me what’s wrong with my body from one appointment? All these “you COULD be” “you MIGHT have”. Why don’t you know? This is your job.

Now, I’m really just anxious. Every time I get a call from the doctor’s I panic. All they’ve had for me these last few months is bad news and uncertainties. It’s frustrating. Lately, my body has been feeling off, and I don’t know if it’s because of the stress/ anxiety that the doctor’s keep piling onto me, or if something truly is wrong with me & they can’t figure it out. 

I’ll list out some of the symptoms I still have even after treatment for Chlamydia + UTI:

Abdominal pain (sometimes sharp)
Extreme fatigue
Diarrhea 
Hacking up phlegm (with no cough)
Anxiety
Poor appetite (I’ve never eaten that much in general)
Slight discomfort when I urinate (like I don’t get all of it out)
Get cold easily
Vaginal discharge (smelly)

If you have any answers for me I’d really appreciate it.
